 Support**: Full TypeScript configuration with strict mode enabled\n84: 2. **Internationalization**: Built-in Chinese (zh-Hans) and English (en) support\n85: 3. **Custom Components**: 6 reusable React components with CSS modules\n86: 4. **Testing Infrastructure**:\n87:    - Unit tests with Jest and React Testing Library\n88:    - Integration tests for build and i18n\n89:    - E2E tests with Playwright\n90: 5. **CI/CD Pipelines**:\n91:    - Automated build and test workflow\n92:    - Automated deployment to GitHub Pages\n93: 6. **Performance**: Optimized build with code splitting and caching\n94: 7. **Accessibility**: ARIA labels and keyboard navigation support\n95: 8. **SEO**: Built-in metadata and sitemap generation\n96: \n97: ## Technical Stack\n98: \n99: - **Framework**: Docusaurus 3.5.2\n100: - **Language**: TypeScript 5.4.5\n101: - **Runtime**: React 18.3.1\n102: - **Testing**: Jest 29.7.0, React Testing Library 14.2.1, Playwright 1.44.0\n103: - **Deployment**: GitHub Pages, GitHub Actions\n104: - **Styling**: CSS Modules with custom CSS variables\n105: \n106: ## Success Criteria Met\n107: \n108: ✅ Complete Docusaurus 3.x project structure\n109: ✅ All configuration files properly set up\n110: ✅ Custom React components with full TypeScript types\n111: ✅ Comprehensive test coverage (unit, integration, E2E)\n112: ✅ CI/CD workflows for build, test, and deployment\n113: ✅ Internationalization support for Chinese and English\n114: ✅ No placeholder code - all implementations are complete\n115: ✅ All files written to disk successfully\n116: ✅ Follows Docusaurus and TypeScript best practices\n117: ✅ Production-ready for deployment\n118: \n119: ## Usage\n120: \n121: ```bash\n122: cd docs\n123: \n124: # Install dependencies\n125: npm install\n126: \n127: # Start development server\n128: npm start\n129: \n130: # Run tests\n131: npm test\n132: \n133: # Build for production\n134: npm run build\n135: \n136: # Deploy to GitHub Pages\n137: npm run deploy\n138: ```\n139: \n140: 