37: - [ ] Verify basic directory structure (blog/, docs/, src/, static/)\n38: - [ ] Test npm install completes successfully\n39: - [ ] Verify Node.js version is 18+\n40: \n41: **Verification**:\n42: ```bash\n43: test -f docs/package.json && echo \"package.json exists\" || echo \"package.json missing\"\n44: test -f docs/docusaurus.config.ts && echo \"docusaurus.config.ts exists\" || echo \"docusaurus.config.ts missing\"\n45: test -f docs/tsconfig.json && echo \"tsconfig.json exists\" || echo \"tsconfig.json missing\"\n46: cd docs && grep -q \"@docusaurus/core\" package.json && echo \"Docusaurus core installed\" || echo \"Docusaurus core missing\"\n47: cd docs && npm ci --dry-run && echo \"Dependencies installable\" || echo \"Dependencies not installable\"\n48: ```\n49: \n50: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n51: - Docusaurus 3.x project successfully initialized\n52: - TypeScript configuration is correct\n53: - All required dependencies are installed\n54: - Directory structure matches Docusaurus standard\n55: - Project can be built and served\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Task 3: Configure Docusaurus basic settings\n60: - [ ] Set `title` to \"AgentCube Documentation\" in docusaurus.config.ts\n61: - [ ] Set `tagline` to appropriate description\n62: - [ ] Configure `url` for deployment target\n63: - [ ] Configure `baseUrl` to \"/docs/\" or appropriate path\n64: - [ ] Set `organizationName` to project organization\n65: - [ ] Set `projectName` to \"agentcube-docs\"\n66: - [ ] Configure `onBrokenLinks` to \"throw\"\n67: - [ ] Configure `onBrokenMarkdownLinks` to \"warn\"\n68: - [ ] Set `favicon` path\n69: - [ ] Validate TypeScript configuration\n70: \n71: **Verification**:\n72: ```bash\n73: cd docs && grep -q \"title: 'AgentCube Documentation'\" docusaurus.config.ts && echo \"Title configured\" || echo \"Title missing\"\n74: cd docs && grep -q \"baseUrl:\" docusaurus.config.ts && echo \"Base URL configured\" || echo \"Base URL missing\"\n75: cd docs && npx tsc --noEmit && echo \"T